      "file_path": "tosca-controlloop/runtime/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/runtime/monitoring/MonitoringProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "question: is it necessary to create all of these XxxList classes?  Wondering why we don't just return the List<Xxx> objects instead and avoid the extra memory and code for doing \"new\" and setXxxList()",
