    },
    {
      "id": "7c904a16_4a920b53",
      "file_path": "tosca-controlloop/runtime/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/runtime/monitoring/MonitoringProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "Hi Jim, We can just return the List here, but I guess we should also change the REST controller response accordingly. We may need to create a new GenericEntity type response and use it on the REST controller methods to accommodate list of entities in the response.\n\nChanges expected on REST controller:\n(-)  @ApiOperation(response = ParticipantStatisticsList.class)\n(+)  @ApiOperation(response = ParticipantStatistics.class, responseContainer = \"List\")\n\n(+)  GenericEntity<List<ParticipantStatistics>> entities = new GenericEntity<List<ParticipantStatistics>>(response){};\n\nReturn the above created GenericEntity type as response entity. Please provide your thoughts if this change can be implemented on the controller.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6070,
        "name": "Ramesh Murugan Iyer",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "ramesh.murugan.iyer@est.tech",
        "username": "rameshiyer27"
      },
      "updated": "2021-03-16 17:17:50.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a7fe9f3a_3f32fbb4",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "f8b4ceac_ba4dd108",
      "file_path": "tosca-controlloop/runtime/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/clamp/controlloop/runtime/monitoring/MonitoringProvider.java",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 84,
      "message": "ah, so this is being returned directly by a REST call rather than being embedded within another returned structure.  That being the case, it's fine left as is.  REST allows generic Lists to be returned, but it seems like it's frequently more convenient to wrap it, as it is here.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 811,
        "name": "Jim Hahn",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jrh3@att.com",
        "username": "jrh3"
      },
